{"key":"processedPost-12539242","value":{"id":12539242,"first":12539186,"last":12542091,"when":1273540649,"utime":"05/11/10 04:17 AM","cleanedPost":"When you shake your jars, you want to separate every kernel of grain from every other one.&nbsp; Bang it on a fully inflated tire, or phone book, etc.&nbsp; If it fails to recover, then it was contaminated with bacteria anyway.&nbsp; Only shake once at around 20% to 30%.<br />Be careful using any lime but hydrated lime for a casing layer.&nbsp; If it comes from dolomite limestone, it can negatively impact fruiting performance due to high Mg.&nbsp; You can use calcium carbonate(ground limestone or oyster shells), but it's only so effective because it needs a month or two to break down, and most casing layers are finished by then.<br />RR"}}